				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$( {\text{CO}}_{ 2} )_{ 2}^{ - }$$\end{document} species, which may then be transformed into an oxalate species, whereby a C–C bond is formed. These oxalate species may then be further catalytically transformed with water or ammonia into useful fuels and other products.
